---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<Layout
  title={`Editorial Policy | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Compute Current editorial standards, source attribution policy, AI-assisted content disclosure, and publication safeguards."
  canonicalPath="/editorial-policy/"
>
  <main class="policy-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Intelligence board</a>
    <article class="policy-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">Editorial Policy</p>
      <h1>Infrastructure intelligence needs source discipline.</h1>
      <p class="policy-lede">
        Compute Current uses automated collection and AI-assisted editorial workflows, but source quality, infrastructure relevance, and repetition safeguards determine what can be published.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>Publication Standard</h2>
        <p>
          We do not publish long-form generated articles from sources that fail extraction quality checks. Low-quality extraction, weak source fidelity, or low infrastructure relevance can result in a short signal card, archive-only treatment, noindex, or blocked publication.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Source Attribution</h2>
        <p>
          Every article page links to the original source. Compute Current keeps its own canonical URL for the generated memo while marking the source article as the basis for analysis through visible attribution and article structured data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>AI-assisted Content Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          AI systems may assist with extraction, relevance classification, taxonomy assignment, summarization, blueprint selection, draft generation, and quality checks. The source article remains the authoritative record, and generated analysis must remain tied to source-specific facts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Quality Gates</h2>
        <p>
          Full Compute Current memos require acceptable source extraction quality, high AI infrastructure relevance, usable expert insight fields, repetition checks, source-fidelity checks, taxonomy checks, and publication decision checks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Language Guardrails</h2>
        <p>
          We avoid generic repeated infrastructure framing. Generated drafts are checked for banned generic phrases, repeated sentence patterns, repeated paragraph structures, heading similarity, blueprint overuse, and conclusion similarity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="policy-link-row" aria-label="Transparency pages">
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>
        <a href="/ai-disclosure/">AI-assisted Disclosure</a>
      </nav>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
